6... e6 { Black frees the e7-square for his bishop. } 7. Qd2
{ White will quickly play long castle and put pressure down the d-file. } 7...
a6
{ This move is very common in the classical sicilian. Black prepares a b5 push and stops a White knight from coming to b5. }
8. O-O-O { The logical follow-up, preparing to put pressure on d6. } 8... Bd7
{ This is the most popular move, clearing the c8-square. } 9. f3 Be7 10. h4
{ White's kingside pawns will quickly become quite bothersome for Black. }
10... h6 11. Be3 h5 { Black prevents an immediate g4 push. } 12. Bg5
{ White has good attacking chances on the kingside. } *

