[Black "Maroczy Bind: 6.Be6 Sideline"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 e5
{ This is known as the Kalashnikov Sicilian. It is similar to the Sveshnikov Sicilian in many ways, but Black has not taken the time to play Nf6 before playing e5. This is an important difference. }
5. Nb5 { White's knight which has just been attacked heads for d6. } 5... d6
{ Black does not want to allow Nd6 so he prevents it by playing d6 himself. }
6. c4
{ This is a very strong way to play against the Kalshnikov. White creates a very firm grip of the d5-square. }
6... Be6
{ This is another way that Black can develop, but it is nothing to worry about. }
7. N1c3 a6 8. Na3 Be7 { We have transposed to the main line. } *

