1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6
{ This move characterizes the Accelerated Dragon. Black prepares to fianchetto his bishop without having played d6. Now White has a very powerful line at his disposal known as the Maroczy Bind. }
5. c4
{ This is known as the Maroczy Bind is part of the reason why the Acclerated Dragon is barely ever played at the top level. White clamps down on the d5-square which prevents any d5 break by Black, and prepares to use his space advantage to win the game. The resulting positions are very transpositional and can result from various move orders. }
5... Nf6
{ This is the alternative to Bg7. It can transpose back to Bg7 lines or lead to entirely different positions. }
6. Nc3 { White protects the e4-pawn. } 6... d6
{ Black prepares to develop his light-squared bishop. } 7. Be2 Nxd4
